      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks, i'll look into using unique_ptr right away. i suspect there's more than one spot where this is happening though, since the leak seems very consistent and slow. \n\nbeyond just the obvious new/delete issues, what are some other ways a leak could hide in a complex system like this? specifically for an embedded environment where i can't just run valgrind or a heavy debugger easily.",
      "source": "evaluator"
